Russian President Vladimir Putin has signed a law imposing administrative liability for the violation of the time and procedure for the payment of goods (work, services) in procurement for State and municipal needs.
This law is intended to address the very acute problem of non-performance by customers in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs could not receive payment under already executed State and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the Russian President instructed the Office of the Attorney-General of the Russian Federation to take the problem into special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not cope with unfair customers who had entered into unfunded contracts, tried to avoid payment obligations and included illegal terms in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office has submitted 9,700 submissions, resulting in disciplinary proceedings against 4,500 officials, administrative proceedings against 533 officials, 75 cases of investigation and 46 cases of investigation.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These huge amounts have not been accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for much more modest amounts have led to huge debts.
Here's the case.
The manager of the small company won a competition for social transport services for several million roubles.
The man invested all his working money, fully fulfilled his obligations, but did not receive the money on time.
The result is an increasing financial coma of salaries, taxes, loans that would have led to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur had not sought the assistance of the prosecutor.
The problem has now been maximized in a number of regions.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total debt on State and municipal contracts identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office operates under manual crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally holds visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, at which all violations revealed by the prosecutors and measures taken to address them without delay are dealt with.
Such operational meetings have already taken place this year in Yaroslavla and Yekaterinburg.
The implementation of Federal Law No. 189-FZ “On the amendment of the Code of Administrative Offences in order to establish the administrative liability of the employer's officials for the violation of the time and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in the procurement of public and municipal needs”, signed by the President of the Russian Federation last week, will improve the public customer's pay discipline.
The draft law was drafted by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Attorney-General ' s Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences with an article which provides for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 roubles for breaching the time limit and procedure for payment of goods, works and services by the employer in State and municipal procurement.
If an official had already been administratively punished for a similar offence, he would be disqualified for a period of between one and two years.
All prosecutors of constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure that these legislative innovations are applied in practice.
Civil Rights Unit announced a travel warning in Missouri.
The National Association for the Advancement of Colored People issued a warning to colored people travelling to Missouri because of discriminatory state policies and racist attacks.
The group's statement is as follows: “The warning to travelers of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, valid until 28 August 2017, encourages African American travelers, guests and citizens of Missouri to be particularly careful and cautious in travelling around the state in connection with a number of suspicious racist incidents that have recently taken place throughout the state and which have been brought here.”
According to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, the recent Missouri law, which made it more difficult for people to win discrimination claims, and the fact that State law enforcement authorities disproportionately targeted minorities.
“You are subject to human rights violations.
They are stopped on the roads because of their skin colour, beaten and killed,” said Rod Chapel, President of the National Association for the Advancement of the Colored Population of Missouri, newspaper Kansas City Star.
“We hear complaints more often than ever.”
This is the first warning of this kind announced by the organization to the U.S. state.
The Group referred to incidents such as the racial humiliation of black students at Missouri University and the death of 20-year-old Tori Sanders, a black man from Tennessee.
Sanders died under suspicious circumstances earlier this year after he ran out of gas on a state trip, and Missouri State Police arrested him without charge of a crime.
The warning also mentions a recent report by the Attorney General of Missouri State that the probability of being stopped on the road for black drivers is 75 per cent higher than for white drivers.
“The aim of the warning is to keep people informed of the situation and to warn their relatives and friends and colleagues about what might happen in Missouri”, said Chapel.
“People must be trained in one way or another, whether they will take the bail money with them or tell their relatives that they are traveling through state territory.”
According to the latest FBI hate crime report, 100 hate crimes were reported in Missouri in 2015, making the state the sixteenth State in terms of the number of such violations.
A travel warning is also a response to the new Missouri State Act, which will make it more difficult to prosecute a legal entity for housing or labour discrimination.
Previously, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) had issued warnings to travelers in Texas and Arizona after these states had enacted new immigration control laws requiring local law enforcement agencies to arrest people for immigration violations, which ACLU believed should have increased the number of racial checks.
Movement warnings are usually issued by the Department of State for other countries, but recently public organizations have resorted to this measure in response to certain laws and trends within the US.
