Kelly told the staff that the information had to go through it -- paper or briefing -- because the president would be better off making decisions if he received the right information.
Kelly's diagnosis is absolutely correct, but others have already failed in trying to keep Trump at bay by tracking the information received.
President Trump's relationship with television developed decades ago -- and now that he's in the White House, his habit of watching TV is still strong.
