Trump read the article and started asking the staff about Welsh."
Goldmacher adds that the then Chief of Staff Raines Pribus and the Secretary of Staff Rob Porter "were trying to build a system to control and document the flow of papers that Trump receives."
How did it work?
Three months later, Kelly's trying to do the same.
He may be a more efficient manager than Pribus, but Trump is still impulsive, and his assistants are still fighting each other for influence.
These constant factors make Kelly's task very difficult.
