In Ukraine, Russians were offered to be sent to prison for illegal border crossing
A draft law has been registered in the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine, according to which Russians may be subject to criminal penalties for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
As RT broadcasts, the document registered in the Ukrainian Parliament's electronic database implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the sentence may be increased to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained at the border with the weapon, the time of detention would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians who had attempted to enter Russia outside the designated crossing points.
